%N A395403 Numbers k such that sigma(k) = psi(k) + tau(k)^3 + Omega(k)^3.
%e A395403 1528 is a term since sigma(1528) = 2880 = 2304 + 8^3 + 4^3 = psi(1528) + tau(1528)^3 + Omega(1528)^3.
%o A395403 (PARI) isok(k) = {my(f = factor(k)); sigma(f) == prod(i=1, #f~, (f[i, 1]+1) * f[i, 1]^(f[i, 2]-1)) + numdiv(f)^3 + bigomega(f)^3; } \\ _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 21 2026
